videos.headline: Pitt opens drive with leaping catch for 38-yard gain
videos.description: Pittsburgh QB Nathan Peterman finds Dontez Ford along the sidelines for a 38-yard gain on the opening drive against Northwestern.

videos.headline: Pitt offensive lineman Brian O'Neill tries to throw a TD pass
videos.description: Brian O'Neill pass incomplete to George Aston

videos.headline: Northwestern stops Pitt with goal-line stand
videos.description: Pitt's James Conner tries to leap over the pile, but Northwestern stops him just short of the goal line.

videos.headline: Northwestern breaks off huge run from own 2-yard line
videos.description: After Northwestern's goal-line stand, Justin Jackson finds a hole up the middle for a 68-yard run.

videos.headline: Jackson dives in for 8-yard Northwestern TD
videos.description: Northwestern RB Justin Jackson dives for the pylon, scoring an 8-yard touchdown to get Northwestern on the board.

videos.headline: Pitt uses flea-flicker to perfection for 37-yard gain
videos.description: Pittsburgh digs into its bag of tricks to complete a 37-yard pass with a flea-flicker.

videos.headline: Northwestern's red-zone defense comes up with interception
videos.description: Pitt QB Nathan Peterman's pass is intercepted by Godwin Igwebuike in the red zone.

videos.headline: Pitt gets timely interception in the end zone
videos.description: Pittsburgh's Avonte Maddox comes down with a timely interception to keep Northwestern from extending its lead.

videos.headline: Northwestern's Jackson scores acrobatic TD
videos.description: Justin Jackson puts his hand down to keep his balance and acrobatically finds his way into the end zone for a 16-yard score.

videos.headline: Pitt's Weah burns defender for 69-yard TD
videos.description: Pitt WR Jester Weah hauls in a pass and takes it 69 yards for the score.

videos.headline: Austin Carr loses his shoe making the tip toe catch
videos.description: Clayton Thorson pass complete to Austin Carr for 8 yds to the Pitt 31

videos.headline: PITT vs. NW
Justin Jackson stiff arms, spins to get close to a 1st down
videos.description: Justin Jackson run for 8 yds to the Pitt 45

videos.headline: Justin Jackson finds space and bolts for 40-yard TD
videos.description: Northwestern RB Justin Jackson finds space and jets downfield for a 40-yard score, his third rushing touchdown of the day.

videos.headline: Pitt blocks Northwestern's punt
videos.description: Pitt's Chawntez Moss gets a hand on Northwestern's punt, to help the Panthers take over deep in the Wildcats' territory.

videos.headline: Pitt converts play-action pass for TD
videos.description: Pitt's Ben DiNucci connects with George Aston on a 6-yard touchdown, giving the Panthers' the lead 24-21.

videos.headline: Northwestern coverts on 4th down with diving catch
videos.description: Clayton Thorson pass complete to Macan Wilson for 5 yds to the Pitt 41 for a 1ST down

videos.headline: Northwestern scores TD on fourth-and-1
videos.description: On fourth-and-1, Northwestern's Clayton Thorson finds a wide-open Garrett Dickerson for a 21-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: Northwestern's defense forces a fumble in the 4th Quarter
videos.description: Quadree Henderson run for 2 yds to the Pitt 27 Quadree Henderson fumbled, forced by Anthony Walker Jr., recovered by Nwest Tyler Lancaster

videos.headline: Northwestern's McGee gets INT in the red zone
videos.description: On fourth-and-10, Pitt's Ben DiNucci throws to the end zone but gets intercepted by Northwestern's Jared McGee to maintain the Wildcats' 31-24 lead.

videos.headline: Another late INT seals victory for Northwestern
videos.description: Minutes after throwing an interception in the red zone, Pitt's Ben DiNucci gets picked off by Kyle Queiro to finish off Northwestern's 31-24 victory.

videos.headline: Fitzgerald has special shout-out for Kanell, ESPN crew
videos.description: After a victory over Pittsburgh in the New Era Pinstripe Bowl, Northwestern coach Pat Fitzgerald makes special mention of Danny Kanell and the ESPN crew, who provided extra motivation for the Wildcats by picking the Panthers to win the game.
